### Clear All Cookies from NextRequest

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/next-request.mdx

Removes the Set-Cookie header from the request, effectively clearing all cookies. Use this to reset all request cookies in a single operation.

```typescript
request.cookies.clear()
```

--------------------------------

### Set Cookie on NextRequest

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/next-request.mdx

Sets a cookie with a given name and value on the incoming request. The cookie is added to the Set-Cookie header with the request path. Useful for modifying request cookies before processing.

```typescript
// Given incoming request /home
// Set a cookie to hide the banner
// request will have a `Set-Cookie:show-banner=false;path=/home` header
request.cookies.set('show-banner', 'false')
```

--------------------------------

### Get Single Cookie from NextRequest

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/next-request.mdx

Retrieves the value of a specific cookie by name from the request. Returns undefined if the cookie is not found, or the first cookie value if multiple cookies with the same name exist.

```typescript
// Given incoming request /home
// { name: 'show-banner', value: 'false', Path: '/home' }
request.cookies.get('show-banner')
```

--------------------------------

### Get All Cookies from NextRequest

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/next-request.mdx

Retrieves all values of a specific cookie by name, or all cookies on the request if no name is provided. Returns an array of cookie objects with name, value, and path properties. Useful for accessing multiple cookies with the same name.

```typescript
// Given incoming request /home
// [
//   { name: 'experiments', value: 'new-pricing-page', Path: '/home' },
//   { name: 'experiments', value: 'winter-launch', Path: '/home' },
// ]
request.cookies.getAll('experiments')
// Alternatively, get all cookies for the request
request.cookies.getAll()
```

--------------------------------

### Check Cookie Existence in NextRequest

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/next-request.mdx

Determines whether a cookie with a given name exists on the request. Returns true if the cookie is present, false otherwise. Useful for conditional logic based on cookie presence.

```typescript
// Returns true if cookie exists, false if it does not
request.cookies.has('experiments')
```

--------------------------------

### Delete Cookie from NextRequest

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/next-request.mdx

Removes a cookie from the request by name. Returns true if a cookie was successfully deleted, or false if no cookie with that name was found on the request.

```typescript
// Returns true for deleted, false is nothing is deleted
request.cookies.delete('experiments')
```

--------------------------------

### Reading Cookies in Next.js API Routes

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/02-pages/03-building-your-application/03-data-fetching/03-forms-and-mutations.mdx

This snippet demonstrates how to read cookies sent with the request within a Next.js API Route. The `req.cookies` object provides access to all incoming cookies as key-value pairs, making it easy to retrieve specific cookie values like an authorization token.

```typescript
import type { NextApiRequest, NextApiResponse } from 'next'

export default async function handler(
  req: NextApiRequest,
  res: NextApiResponse
) {
  const auth = req.cookies.authorization
  // ...
}
```

```javascript
export default async function handler(req, res) {
  const auth = req.cookies.authorization
  // ...
}
```

