### Read cookies from `NextRequest` using Web APIs in Next.js API routes

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/03-file-conventions/route.mdx

This snippet shows how to access cookies directly from the `request.cookies` property of a `NextRequest` object, leveraging underlying Web APIs. This method provides an alternative way to read cookies from the incoming request.

```ts
import { type NextRequest } from 'next/server'

export async function GET(request: NextRequest) {
  const token = request.cookies.get('token')
}
```

```js
export async function GET(request) {
  const token = request.cookies.get('token')
}
```

